---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
import PromptTool from '../components/PromptTool.tsx';
---

<ToolPage
  title="Read an LLM Prompt From Your Logs — Prompt Log Formatter"
  description="Pulled a prompt out of your application logs and it's an unreadable escaped line? Paste it here to get a clean, role-by-role conversation. Free prompt log formatter, in-browser."
  h1="Read a Prompt From Your Logs"
  intro="AI engineers log their prompts to debug them — but in the console they arrive as one giant escaped line with the roles mashed together. Paste that log line here and get a clean, readable conversation back."
  path="/read-prompt-from-logs"
>
  <PromptTool client:only="react" />

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">The logged-prompt problem</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      You add a <code>console.log</code> or a logger line to see exactly what you're sending the
      model. Then you open the logs and it's unreadable: <code>\n</code> everywhere instead of line
      breaks, JSON payloads crammed inline, and the system, user and assistant turns fused into one
      wall of text. Figuring out what actually went to the model means hand-unescaping a string.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Paste the log line, read the prompt</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      This tool does the untangling for you — it unescapes the newlines and quotes, pretty-prints
      inline JSON, and splits each role into its own labeled, color-coded block, so a copied log line
      becomes a conversation you can scan in seconds.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">FAQ</h2>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Can I paste production logs?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      Yes — nothing leaves your browser, so real production prompts and data stay private.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Which APIs work?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      OpenAI, Claude and other LLM formats. See
      <a class="text-brand-600 underline" href="/format-openai-prompt">OpenAI</a> and
      <a class="text-brand-600 underline" href="/format-claude-prompt">Claude</a> guides.
    </p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>
